data.content:
The core issue is that .NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which targets **OpenAPI 3.1** (JSON Schema–based). Here are the breaking changes and fixes:

### 1. `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace removed
All `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. are gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead.

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `OpenApiSchema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI 3.1 expresses nullability via the type system (e.g., `type: ["string", "null"]`). The `Nullable` property no longer exists on `OpenApiSchema`. The `Type` property is now a **flags enum** (`JsonSchemaType`).

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After — remove the null flag from the type
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;

// (To make something nullable, you'd do:)
// property.Value.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

You'll need:
```csharp
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;  // JsonSchemaType is here
```

### 3. `OpenApiResponse`, `OpenApiSecurityScheme`, `OpenApiReference`
These remain largely the same in v2 — `Responses.TryAdd(...)`, `ReferenceType.SecurityScheme`, and the `OpenApiSecurityRequirement` dictionary pattern should still compile.

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;       // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");   // was OpenApiString
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;  // was .Nullable = false
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1 / OpenAPI 3.0) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2 / OpenAPI 3.1) |
|---|---|
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `new OpenApiArray { ... }` | `new JsonArray { ... }` |
| `new OpenApiObject { ... }` | `new JsonObject { ... }` |
